reviews.text: Lovely lady at reception full of knowledge! Well worth the $5

Always very interesting for all ages they have an area that is designed to keep children amused,upstairs the was a very interesting collection of photos and facts about the immigration into Australia since it started the are also some outer buildings that have been given new life this is all next door to a replica of the ship that 1st brought life to Albany
Lots of interesting bits and pieces just watch your noggin on the doorways the people of old must of been very short!

This is an incredible display of the earliest days of Albany's penal past. The history is exceptionally displayed and explained. The collection of artifacts is something else and a credit to the historical society of Albany and the local and state governments.

This facility provides a valuable insight into the early settlement of Albany. The gaol is filled with antiques and historical collections that take you back in time. The displays are well presented and provides an authentic oversight of of years past and the convicts who were incarcerated in this Gaol. The preservation of this important facility is a credit to the historical society and relevant government agencies.

Really fun VR experience will take you around Albany before you go yourself. Great way to determine if you want to go see a place or not, as well as really fun for all ages. The staff was friendly and helpful - they know the drill and will show you the places you forget to ask about. The visitor center is also attached to the library, so you can check that out while you're there.
Staff very helpful and friendly. You must try the 3D goggles at the 3D display.
Very helpful and a good place to visit.  Now all 3 Centres are helping each other with The Amazing South Coast.  Albany, Denmark, Mt Barker, the triangle...
New location is great. Staff very helpful. Plenty of advice and souvenirs.

Had some extremely helpful members in the visitors center who were able to give us loaded of info. They will also help you book tours etc. The visitors center is very modern as well will VR goggles and touch screens to view different activities.

Great to get do close to turbines. The sound is remarkable.  Excellent information posted along the pathway. The pathways are solid and easy. Terrific off shoot from the Bibbulmun Track. The lookout platforms allow great views of the coast and the rain clouds. There is a toilet on site.
Pretty cool if your into a green earth. The interpetational guides were great. If you got it in you hike to the lookout. It is well worth the effort. Toilets get C
Where the rigid coastline meets the rugged landscape. Good walking tracks, wind turbines and scenic views of the great southern basin.
Beautiful tourist location on southern coast of Albany. It's 24 hours accessible and parking is free. Also available are hang gliding and kite sports nearby but only during day.
Always good. Love going back there. Great view and walks

Patrick Taylor cottage is on Duke street is old dwelling in western Australia its garden is the best looking the Old carts are worth looking at the old the extensive collection of period costumes and household goods it is worth looking at so is the garden the staff is very helpful to
Very informative good display worth a visit
Lovely old home and lots of history
Good history
Full of early days memorobelia, thoughtfully preserved and well worth a visit. Great for a better understanding of local history.
Great opportunities to be attended as well as exhibitions etc in having a art center in Albany
Drawing group on Mondays is fun.
Great heritage listed building with some classy stalls and great art
Brilliant historic building, very well looked after, interesting artworks etc, fabulous views
So helpful

The restaurant, "Lime 303" is superb.
We  had 6 of the share tasting plates between 3 people. Everything was excellent, no wonder they have won several Gold Plate awards over the years.

Wonderful suite, well appointed and immaculately clean. Very comfortable and a really lovely treat.  Restaurant was very good, imaginative local menu for dinner and breakfasts were also great. Staff extremely helpful and welcoming, we will remember this stay for a long time.
Great location, quiet room. Easy and fast check in. Friendly service. Very clean room with all amenities provided. Awesome view if you get the balcony overlooking town.

I was initially skeptical of staying here (despite the good reviews), expecting the rooms to be dated and "well-used". However, on arrival I was very pleasantly surprised to find a good sized room with fairly new furniture and a newly renovated bathroom. Everything was very clean and we received great service from all staff when we required any extra assistance. We had only booked one night but after such a nice stay on the first night we decided to extend our stay. 

I definitely would stay again and recommend to others
Room was good, a little old fashioned with a 70s feel. But clean and tidy and everything you need. Great location and excellent breakfast

Beautiful beach front location with a kids playground right there so you can eat and watch the kids at the same time. Service was quick too. The sweet potato gnocchi was very unique and large portions!

The food is delicious. I recommend the vegan burger. They are great if you have allergies or dietary requirements. It is busy, nevertheless, the atmosphere is nice & kid friendly. Some of the staff can be quite obnoxious and have been consistently. Aside from that, I highly recommend Three Anchors.

Come in, get seated at a dirty table and we have to clean it ourselves... ordered the scotch filet, chicken wings, 1 coke and glass of wine. Saw the drinks get circled around the restaurant and was not dropped off to us after 15 minutes of ordering. 5 minutes later we get our food and it’s cold! The steak was covered in fat and the butter was still cold as a rock. My chicken wings tasted like left over Woolworth microwave chicken wings you get from the frozen aisle. 

The only extra star was for the server who up-sale by asking me if I wanted prawns with my steak! She wins for making an effort for an extra buck! I worked in the restaurant industry and she was the only positive to your restaurant. Drives me nuts because there’s so much potential!!!

Three Anchors is located on the foreshore at Middleton Beach one of the most Iconic spots in the Albany Area. The views are Simply Amazing  and the Ambience of the indoor and outdoor areas is great. It is always busy and popular with families and most peaple. The menu is great and the food as well. Coffee is fantastic. It is all in all a great place for all tastes. And you can always have a swim before or after. Love it. Cheers. 😊

As per Michelin star ratings, 2 stars: worth taking a short detour. World-class seafood paired with world-class local wines with unpretentious service and priceless view. Even great for kids, with an activity pack available and a playground right outside. Adults can actually enjoy a quality adult meal while their children are entertained.

Great breakfast. Fantastic. Nice service. Excellent quality food. Been twice. Will be back when in Albany. - Now 6 weeks later I was there for an early dinner at 4 today and would give them another 5 stars if I could.

Lovely kit out, well staffed attended all our needs ,food - steak burger was nice 2 pieces of beef not chewy , chicken schnitzel below average looked like Coles deli heart shaped chicken dry and over cooked (ping In microwave) packet potato , coffees were beautiful and takeaway cakes were 5/5.

Good for simple, diner-style food like burgers, sandwiches, a few salads and coffee. The staff are friendly and when we were there worked non stop turning tables over, accommodating all new customers efficiently and to their seating preferences. They took order quickly and it came out quickly too.
For me the atmosphere was a bit lacking (hence not 5 stars) and the interior of this diner feels a bit dated. They did seem to attract a bit of an older crowd. 
FYI no lamb on the menu. 
They also have a slightly simplified and cheaper takeaway menu.
Good food at good prices. Great coffee and excellent burgers! Child friendly too
Pleasant eatery, with a good selection of drinks, light meals and ambience. Popular. Access is possibly hard for wheelchairs. Service is prompt and pleasant. Parking in the street or nearby.
Was expecting more Vegan, vegetarian options,but only one option on menu which didn't appeal.Very disappointed , didn't stay ,went up the street to a little cafe .

Amazing! Food was brilliant, maybe the best meal we have ever had in Australia! Two friends and I went, we all had something different and were all so impressed, it was reasonably priced for the food that we got, service was friendly, restaurant was quite busy and we didn’t have to wait long at all, the chef then came out at the end to help the waitresses and he was so friendly too!
One of the best meals I have ever had. The flavours complimented each other. The menus was varied and was hard to choose just one thing!
Great food at a really reasonable price. Very good service. Would not hesitate to recommend as one of the better places to dine out at in Albany.

So me and my family went for a birthday dinner and at the start the customer service was average the waitress missed half of our group when asking us for the order of drinks. Then when we ordered our food it took nearly an hour to get to us. And the food was amazing but I personally thought the wait was way to long!!
Was expecting more Vegan, vegetarian options,but only one option on menu which didn't appeal.Very disappointed , didn't stay ,went up the street to a little cafe .

Then when we ordered our food it took nearly an hour to get to us. And the food was amazing but I personally thought the wait was way to long!!
Great food,ordered take out delivery  arrived within 1/2 hour,very flavorful  ,had shrimp/broccoli  orange chicken, 4 shrimp egg ,definitely will order again when in town,🥢🍝
The food is great, fast delivery and always so friendly

Placed an order for three entrees and was told it would be delivered 30 to 45 minutes. I called every 15 minutes after that and it took an hour and 45 minutes to arrive. I asked to cancel my order as we were in a hurry to get somewhere that night. The lady on the phone would not give me a refund and argued with me stating  he would arrive at any moment. The guy delivered 15 minutes later, and handed ME a $5 bill. Terrible customer service. Would never recommend this place.
I loved this place back in the day. It just seems like once the kids take over or a different set of people take over, it changes and it's never the same. I don't go here anymore becuz of that

Just got my order in it did take about a hour but when i put my order in she did inform me it could be 45- 1hr but it was definitely worth the wait everything taste so good everything taste so fresh and hot definitely packaged so well, will be ordering again.
Super fast, friendly service. Best McDonalds service I've experienced. Great team here.

Amazingly quick service and a spotless and comfortable environment. If my dad asks where do you want to go to lunch I always pick here! I also love the free wifi because my wifi isn’t the quickest and definitely isn’t free. The only thing that could make it better is if you’d deliver.

Crowded but ok. Plenty of room. The eating space seemed a bit desolate. The outback eat space was exposed to the screeches of children rampaging through the play area due to the split glass wall. The non verbal hominid screaming is a worry but not confined to MacDonalds.
They give me a Triple patty Cheese burger, Chips with something on it and sprite frozen something. That cost $13.35 which is worth it. Keep doing Maccas
Same as every McDonald's, cold chips and just edible burger. Coffee was good though. 2 stars for the Coffee.
Great cafe in the main Street of Albany. Great service and great decor. Food yummy.

It's very easy to access just on main Street .Corner shop and remind me like home style 
You can enjoy your coffee and watch passing people
Popies it is a good cafe to have food and drink
Great service, very pleasant.
Friendly staff but really underwhelming coffee

Unbelievable steak house. Top quality food and super top quality service. The waiters and bar staff are unbelievable. It's a reflection of how good the management of the restaurant are.
We had fantastic steaks, the food was delivered to all 6 of us simultaneously. Top quality presentation, and perfectly food. A special mention for Matt our waiter, and Connor the bar man, they are fantastic. We unfortunately did not get a chance to taste Connor's O'Jesus drink concoction. But it sounded wonderful. Cannot recommend Rustlers any higher.

Awesome Fish of the Day. Huge place with excellent service even at it's peak time. Lovely night out. Casual & Tasty. Great selection of local wines & drinks. If you love a Steak - this is your go to place.

Chicken and Ribs. The char grilled chicken breast meat was well cooked. The sear marks on the meat simply add to perfection. The rib was absolutely tasty and simply melted in the mouth. The salad was fresh. The baked potato was awesome as it was very soft. Kids will love it. There were no undercooked hard lumps or overcooked burn smell. Despite the wait was about 75 minutes due to the crowd but the food was cooked to perfection. Nothing was compromised. I enjoyed everything on the plate and I would said it was worth the wait.

Boy these guys know how to cook steak. We got all our meals the way we ordered them, medium rare. The meals are huge. Staff are polite and are proficient about everything they have on offer. Highly recommend .

Nice , tasty and well presented food in reasonable portions.
Variety of food is good 
Good selection of wine and beer.
Large , clean restaurant with a lot of seating for couples and groups.
Family friendly 
Staff were happy , helpful and polite.
A bit up there in price for Albany,, but worth it if you can afford to. 
Just a short walk from the main Street in town. 
Limited car parking space at the front, however lots of parking across the road.
Since new owners have taken over it is now a much better restaurant.
I recommend you try this place if in Albany.
Best ever Indian restaurant. Very indulgent. Friendly service. Clean restaurant. Delicious food. Will return!
The Best Indian food in Albany. I am new to Albany and have tried all 3 local Indian restaurants.. The Tandoori is easily my favourite. huge portions of great food
Just go there. Service, menu and drink, wines, beer, cocktails, topshelf all good price. Quality of the food was excellent, and I've been to India. Come on just do it.
The food was good. A bit too busy lacked a little in attention. Will try it once more to see if it was a blip in service.

Amazingly delicious cuisine, friendly and efficient service, great vakue, lovely ambience, byo and oh so satisfying. Highly recommended for family or for a group of friends, the banquet is divine! I can't wait to return. Best Indian in Albany, no doubt about it.

Good selective menu. Delicious food, never had a bad meal and decent serves.  Guy and the girls are a joy always happy and helpful.  Recommend booking of course and visitors will love cheers ex donut man Graeme Male and Bea x

Being Italian, I can sometimes be fussy with Italian food...not this time...this food was fabulous!  Full of flavour, the traditional big serves and great sized kids meals too.  Service was perfect! Great dine out experience for our family.  Thank you!
Been here many times, is probably my wife and I's favourite restaurant. Relaxed atmosphere good food and great service.
Warm, cosy & family-friendly vibes. Melt-in-your-mouth, authentic Italian cuisine. Felt like I was at my Nonna's house 😊 (portion sizes were about as big!); 10/10 would return/recommend.

Delicious food, perfect service, above what we were expecting from a cosy little restaurant. Wait staff were extremely polite and professional. The Pork Belly serving was huge and the entire dish was fantastic. 10/10. Well done.
Best ever Indian restaurant. Very indulgent. Friendly service. Clean restaurant. Delicious food. Will return!
